<paragraph blockId="66.[151,1436,907,1085]" pageId="66" pageNumber="263">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,273,945,971]" pageId="66" pageNumber="263">Notes.</emphasis>
The presence in 
<collectingRegion box="[494,591,946,972]" country="Italy" name="Sardegna" pageId="66" pageNumber="263">Sardinia</collectingRegion>
of this alien species of Nearctic origin, known from mainland 
<collectingCountry box="[1382,1436,946,972]" name="Italy" pageId="66" pageNumber="263">Italy</collectingCountry>
(Abruzzi), 
<collectingCountry box="[280,360,983,1009]" name="France" pageId="66" pageNumber="263">France</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[418,484,983,1009]" name="Spain" pageId="66" pageNumber="263">Spain</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Mazur, S." box="[500,650,983,1009]" pageId="66" pageNumber="263" refId="ref74858" refString="Mazur, S. (2004) Histeridae. In: Lobl, I. &amp; Smetana, A. (Eds), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera, Volume 2. Hydrophiloidea - Staphylinoidea. Apollo Books, Stenstrup, pp. 68 - 102." type="book" year="2004">Mazur 2004</bibRefCitation>
), was not confirmed by the examination of the various collections, nor is it documented in the literature (Tab. 1) apart from the record in 
<bibRefCitation author="Yelamos, T. &amp; Lackner, T." box="[967,1311,1021,1047]" pageId="66" pageNumber="263" refId="ref77231" refString="Yelamos, T. &amp; Lackner, T. (2004) Fauna Europaea: Histeridae. In: Alonso-Zarazaga, M. A. (Ed.), Fauna Europaea: Coleoptera 1. Fauna Europaea version 1.1, available at http: // www. faunaeur. org [accessed September 2009 as version 1.3 of April 19 th 2007.]" type="url" year="2004">Yélamos and Lackner (2004)</bibRefCitation>
, the origin of which is unknown.
</paragraph>
